{"info": {"author": "Simon Willison", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# asgi-csrf\n\n[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/asgi-csrf.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/asgi-csrf/)\n[![CircleCI](https://circleci.com/gh/simonw/asgi-csrf.svg?style=svg)](https://circleci.com/gh/simonw/asgi-csrf)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache%202.0-blue.svg)](https://github.com/simonw/asgi-csrf/blob/master/LICENSE)\n\nASGI middleware for protecting against CSRF attacks\n\n**This is a preview release - do not assume that this is robust and secure just yet.**\n\n## Installation\n\n    pip install asgi-csrf\n\n## Background\n\nSee the [OWASP guide to Cross Site Request Forgery (CSRF)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/csrf) and their [Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://owasp.org/www-project-cheat-sheets/cheatsheets/Cross-Site_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet).\n\nThis middleware implements the Double Submit Cookie pattern, where a cookie is set that is then compared to a `csrftoken` hidden form field or a `x-csrftoken` HTTP header.\n\n## Limitations\n\n* Brand new. Not extensively tested. Do not trust this yet.\n* Currently only works for `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` forms, not `multipart/form-data` forms (with file uploads)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/simonw/asgi-csrf", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache License, Version 2.0", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "asgi-csrf", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/asgi-csrf/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/asgi-csrf/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/simonw/asgi-csrf"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/asgi-csrf/0.2.2a0/", "requires_dist": ["pytest ; extra == 'test'", "pytest-asyncio ; extra == 'test'", "httpx ; extra == 'test'", "starlette ; extra == 'test'", "python-multipart ; extra == 'test'"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "ASGI middleware for protecting against CSRF attacks", "version": "0.2.2a0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>asgi-csrf</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/asgi-csrf/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PyPI\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/5ea1c45282597bd47b2fc566d7782aef7477089f/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f762f617367692d637372662e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://circleci.com/gh/simonw/asgi-csrf\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"CircleCI\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/1b33bbd63f95a7bfe69460d93a5c61f2754d7864/68747470733a2f2f636972636c6563692e636f6d2f67682f73696d6f6e772f617367692d637372662e7376673f7374796c653d737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/asgi-csrf/blob/master/LICENSE\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"License\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/bad0ad2a7195b40874e3a10488118122d89489fd/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c6963656e73652d417061636865253230322e302d626c75652e737667\"></a></p>\n<p>ASGI middleware for protecting against CSRF attacks</p>\n<p><strong>This is a preview release - do not assume that this is robust and secure just yet.</strong></p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install asgi-csrf\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Background</h2>\n<p>See the <a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/csrf\" rel=\"nofollow\">OWASP guide to Cross Site Request Forgery (CSRF)</a> and their <a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-project-cheat-sheets/cheatsheets/Cross-Site_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) Prevention Cheat Sheet</a>.</p>\n<p>This middleware implements the Double Submit Cookie pattern, where a cookie is set that is then compared to a <code>csrftoken</code> hidden form field or a <code>x-csrftoken</code> HTTP header.</p>\n<h2>Limitations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Brand new. Not extensively tested. Do not trust this yet.</li>\n<li>Currently only works for <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code> forms, not <code>multipart/form-data</code> forms (with file uploads)</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6731236, "releases": {"0.1a0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "05238e858630c2f44a0cd75115f2b3a0", "sha256": "34702baea225b7bbafd54a9370857acb05d0bf3017d63a8bb022cec10defee03"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "asgi_csrf-0.1a0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "05238e858630c2f44a0cd75115f2b3a0", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 7796, "upload_time": "2020-03-01T23:39:59", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-01T23:39:59.101511Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/5e/da/024a0549cc1adf6c4d1c4b843f0b4b767a82c89ceeb76d8592ba05844065/asgi_csrf-0.1a0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}], "0.2.1a0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6a6656f62f7e0efaa5bdae1247e1e899", "sha256": "6da1f0700a55b5209c8bda61daec5b97620fa8ed4a349465e53bea69437b4341"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "asgi_csrf-0.2.1a0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6a6656f62f7e0efaa5bdae1247e1e899", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 7822, "upload_time": "2020-03-02T03:32:03", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-02T03:32:03.260255Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/28/7f/c11c698ab37bbb8265afdeb9c3b461eeaabf00533548f81ffa5bc015fbec/asgi_csrf-0.2.1a0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}], "0.2.2a0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c5d21f5136675ea4bd45e42e1d84ae68", "sha256": "3d99bdb2fc81180a8fd8ca15433de2e94eb0b9ed71bc752893213cdc5dcab70c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "asgi_csrf-0.2.2a0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c5d21f5136675ea4bd45e42e1d84ae68", "packagetype": "bdist